      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To counter the charge of xenophobia, a debater must firmly pivot the discussion from prejudice to policy and national self-interest. They should argue that the defense of sovereignty and the maintenance of a stable society are not inherently prejudiced acts, but rather necessary functions of governance. By framing the debate around the *function* of a nation-state—protecting its citizens and upholding its laws—they can logically separate policy necessity from bigotry.",
      "source": "target",
